WEBVTT

00:00.034 --> 00:10.745
I am going to read to you the words that are to be found in Paul's Epistle to the Romans in chapter 11, reading from verse 16 to verse 22.

00:12.147 --> 00:18.874
From verse 16 to verse 22, in the 11th chapter, Paul's Epistle to the Romans.

00:18.894 --> 00:22.818
For if the first fruit be holy, the lump is also holy.

00:23.599 --> 00:26.322
And if the root be holy, so are the branches.

00:27.522 --> 00:48.446
And if some of the branches be broken off, and them being a wild olive tree were graphed in among them, and with them particist of the root and fatness of the olive tree, burst not against the branches, but if thou burst thou bearest not the root, but the root thee.

00:49.407 --> 00:55.474
Thou will say, then, the branches were broken off that I might be graphed in, well,

00:56.066 --> 01:02.152
Because of unbelief, they were broken off, and thou standest by faith.

01:03.053 --> 01:04.775
Be not high-minded, but fear.

01:05.856 --> 01:23.474
For if God spared not the natural branches, take heed lest he also spare not thee, behold therefore the goodness and severity of God, on them which fell of severity, but on thee, but toward thee, goodness.

01:24.066 --> 01:26.669
if they will continue in His goodness.

01:27.450 --> 01:31.134
Otherwise, they will also shall be cut off."

01:31.154 --> 01:40.765
Now, we've been engaged for two or three Friday evenings in examining in particular verses 18 to 22.

01:42.067 --> 01:51.538
But I read from the beginning of verse 16, in order that we might have the full statement in our minds as we come to consider this

01:52.034 --> 01:56.659
the particular aspect of this statement that I'm anxious to put before you this evening.

01:57.220 --> 02:09.333
I've suggested that the best way of dividing this statement from the beginning of verse 18 to the end of verse 22 is first and foremost, of course, to deal with pure matters of exposition, which we've done.

02:09.874 --> 02:15.000
Then secondly, I said we must extract the teaching or the doctrine.

02:15.901 --> 02:20.466
And well, to the best of our ability, we've also done that.

02:20.866 --> 02:46.619
Then I suggested that the third heading would be this, the problem raised by this statement and having dealt with it, we hope to go on to consider the general application of this teaching to the situation in which we find ourselves as members of the Christian Church in this extraordinary age in which we live.

02:47.179 --> 02:49.362
But what's before us tonight particularly

02:49.666 --> 02:55.854
is this question of the problem which is raised by this statement.

02:55.874 --> 02:58.357
Now, you notice the way in which I am putting it.

02:59.959 --> 03:18.002
I am not saying that the apostle himself raises the problem, but I am saying that what the apostle says raises the problem in the minds of all the students of the scriptures, and in the case of some people particularly so.

03:19.362 --> 03:28.832
Now, the problem that is raised is raised, of course, by the actual statement of historic fact, which the apostle makes.

03:29.713 --> 03:36.821
It is a shell fact of history that the Jews, speaking generally, were not in the Christian church.

03:37.602 --> 03:47.673
These people of God, of whom we read so much in the Old Testament and were looking forward to the coming of the Messiah, are not in the Christian church speaking generally.

03:48.193 --> 03:49.074
They are outside.

03:49.186 --> 03:57.476
Indeed, he makes the specific statement that they have been broke enough, and we've been considering that.

03:57.677 --> 04:00.540
So that in itself raises a problem.

04:01.321 --> 04:07.429
How does it come to pass that the people of God themselves, as it were, are excluded, cut off?

04:08.510 --> 04:16.680
And are in this condition which is described in extensive by the apostle in this particular chapter.

04:16.700 --> 04:18.162
But over and above,

04:19.586 --> 04:25.635
the raising of the problem by the actual events with which they are confronted.

04:26.756 --> 04:39.374
The problem is raised in an acute form by the explicit statement which we have in verse 22, where the apostles has behold therefore the goodness and severity of God.

04:39.394 --> 04:44.762
Now that is what we were considering, you remember last Friday night on the teaching, but here is the problem.

04:45.763 --> 04:47.826
On them which fell severity

04:48.002 --> 04:58.819
But toward the goodness, if thou continue in his goodness, otherwise thou also shalt be cut off.

04:58.839 --> 05:05.108
There is where the problem, I say, is raised for us in an explicit manner.

05:06.250 --> 05:07.552
It is implicit in the history.

05:07.993 --> 05:12.480
Here it is explicitly stated and put before us.

05:12.500 --> 05:14.002
Very well then, what is the problem?

05:15.170 --> 05:18.054
We can describe it as being a kind of double problem.

05:19.936 --> 05:22.239
But essentially, of course, it's only one.

05:23.000 --> 05:28.787
But it comes before us here in a double manner.

05:28.807 --> 05:40.082
First of all, is nothing a puzzle suggesting in this paragraph that it is our faith and belief after all that saves us.

05:41.503 --> 05:43.506
Now, he appears to be saying that doesn't he?

05:44.290 --> 05:52.341
He says, though we'll say that the branches were broken off that I might be grafted in, well, because of unbelief.

05:53.162 --> 05:56.667
They were broken off, and thou standest by faith.

05:58.329 --> 06:00.172
There, the suggestion seems to be.

06:01.254 --> 06:05.339
That after all, the thing that rarely counts and matters is our faith.

06:06.381 --> 06:10.226
They're out because they didn't believe, we are in because we do believe.

06:11.428 --> 06:13.170
He seems, therefore, to be suggesting

06:13.570 --> 06:22.084
that our faith and belief are a kind of work, and that this is the thing that determines whether we are saved or not.

06:23.666 --> 06:37.228
And secondly, is he not suggesting also in this teaching that it is our faith that also keeps us in salvation?

06:37.248 --> 06:40.914
Or if you prefer it, is he not teaching that we can fall from grace?

06:42.658 --> 06:48.864
And that there is no such doctrine as the doctrine of the final preservation of the saints.

06:49.645 --> 06:50.866
These are his words.

06:51.306 --> 06:58.973
He says, toward the goodness, if thou continue in his goodness, otherwise thou also shall picketh off.

06:59.374 --> 07:02.937
If you don't continue in his goodness, you shall picketh off.

07:03.478 --> 07:12.466
So if you're not cut off, it's because you have continued in his goodness, and to continue in his goodness means this, that you recognize it.

07:12.770 --> 07:14.933
that you believe it, that you are faith in it.

07:15.534 --> 07:34.059
But he seems to be saying that what rarely determines our continuance and persistence in the faith and our final perseverance and preservation is our own continually, our act of belief, our act of faith.

07:34.079 --> 07:39.887
Now there is the problem which I say can be divided up like that way into two aspects.

07:40.268 --> 07:41.810
What is it that brings us in?

07:42.370 --> 07:44.574
What is it that keeps us in?

07:44.594 --> 07:50.523
And the apostle seems to be suggesting on the surface that it is our faith in both instances.

07:51.144 --> 07:54.830
And then of course, the problem that is posed to us is this.

07:56.092 --> 08:07.009
Is the apostle therefore not here contradicting blankly what he himself has taught so plainly and so clearly in other parts of this epistle?

08:07.330 --> 08:10.034
Isn't it indeed the whole object of the epistle to establish?

08:10.146 --> 08:12.689
the doctrine of justification by faith only.

08:13.530 --> 08:16.694
How can that be reconciled with what he says here?

08:17.716 --> 08:38.322
Or how can we reconcile what he has told us so clearly and plainly on the matters of assurance and perseverance with this extraordinary statement here in this 22nd verse, which is only staying, as I say, explicitly what we know to be true in the case of the children of Israel

08:38.626 --> 08:42.350
speaking generally of them as a nation as an actual fact.

08:43.191 --> 08:45.373
So, the question that is before us is this.

08:46.394 --> 09:06.354
Is this statement not a sheer contradiction of what the apostle has been teaching about election, about assurance and about perseverance, the final perseverance and the safety eternally of the saints?

09:07.330 --> 09:22.956
This, of course, is the problem that is raised, and you will find we just have to read the number of commentaries by different people, belonging to different schools to see at once that they're divided into the two groups, and there are many who have been perplexed and troubled by this.

09:23.517 --> 09:31.570
Some, because they're pleased to find a contradiction in the apostles, they think, and that supports their view that he was no more divinely inspired,

09:31.682 --> 09:35.907
than any men today may be inspired and that after all it's only his opinion.

09:36.308 --> 09:41.995
They find in it what they think is a great argument against the whole doctrine of inspiration.

09:42.676 --> 09:48.143
Then there are the party men who use it just to show that they're right after all.

09:48.303 --> 09:51.267
But I'm really not concerned about either of those groups.

09:51.728 --> 09:56.815
I'm concerned about those who find in this genuine difficulty and perplexity.

09:57.676 --> 09:59.538
And it is in order to help them

09:59.810 --> 10:01.832
that we now shall proceed.

10:02.473 --> 10:14.084
God forbid, let me say once more that we should approach this doctrine, this matter here, in any kind of party, prejudice, sectarian spirit.

10:14.784 --> 10:29.138
We should have one desire only, and that is to understand the teaching of the scriptures, that we may glorify God and in order that our souls may be established in the faith and

10:29.218 --> 10:34.066
We are not here simply to support a cause or a party.

10:34.146 --> 10:40.937
We are here to worship God and to glorify His name and to try to arrive at an understanding of His teaching.

10:41.177 --> 10:41.958
Very well.

10:41.978 --> 10:44.522
How do you approach a problem like this?

10:44.542 --> 10:48.108
We've had to do it before, actually, in earlier parts of this same epistle.

10:48.448 --> 10:57.042
But as the Apostle raises it again like this indirectly, he doesn't raise it, as I say, but the statement raises it in the minds of men and women.

10:57.282 --> 10:59.805
As it's raised for us, how do we approach it?

11:00.786 --> 11:03.249
Well, now I suggest this kind of method.

11:04.550 --> 11:14.342
And let me say that this kind of method applies not only with this particular problem, but with any such problem or any similar problem.

11:16.364 --> 11:20.669
Nothing is so important as that we should know how to face problem.

11:21.710 --> 11:25.234
And the method seems to me to be more or less always the same.

11:26.018 --> 11:27.239
Well, how do we do it here?

11:27.279 --> 11:28.981
Well, the first thing I would suggest is this.

11:29.902 --> 11:30.863
Start with your facts.

11:31.863 --> 11:34.566
And there they are perfectly plain and clear before you.

11:35.327 --> 11:41.272
This is a tremendous fact in the story of the children of Israel, the Jew.

11:41.973 --> 11:44.395
Now, the apostle has put that performance.

11:44.475 --> 11:45.837
There's no difficulty about that.

11:46.217 --> 11:49.680
This is a sheer fact, and it's a fact of history.

11:50.741 --> 11:55.005
If they use argument about that, or you just accept it, you've got to face it.

11:55.025 --> 11:55.826
And there it is.

11:57.218 --> 12:00.082
Very well, what's the next step?

12:00.102 --> 12:03.187
Well, I believe the next step is this.

12:04.910 --> 12:11.780
That we must see that the statement is not only made here, but made elsewhere.

12:12.581 --> 12:15.205
The statement concerning the same facts.

12:15.646 --> 12:20.874
Now, let's have a look at the way in which our Lord has stated the same kind of thing.

12:20.994 --> 12:23.417
Let me just pick out one or two.

12:23.437 --> 12:26.482
Take, for instance, what you get in Matthew 8.

12:26.946 --> 12:28.548
and in verse 12.

12:31.413 --> 12:34.657
Or take verse 11 with it, Matthew waits 11 and 12.

12:35.799 --> 12:46.635
Our Lord says, I say unto you, that many shall come from the east and west and shall sit down with Abraham and Isaac and Jacob in the kingdom of heaven.

12:47.957 --> 12:52.664
But the children of the kingdom shall be cast into outer darkness.

12:53.465 --> 12:56.850
There shall be weeping and gnashing of teeth.

12:57.154 --> 13:02.540
You notice the emphasis is that these people are going to come from all parts of the world.

13:02.580 --> 13:17.736
They're going to come from the east and the west, all round as it were, but the children of the kingdom are going to be cast into outer darkness where there shall be weeping and gnashing of teeth.

13:19.097 --> 13:23.602
Then there's a similar statement in Mark 1313.

13:26.018 --> 13:44.483
which doesn't deal so directly with that, but well, perhaps in order to keep it clear in your mind, let me give you the parallel in Luke 1st, take Luke 13, 28, Luke 13, 28, where our Lord again is dealing with the same point.

13:44.503 --> 13:53.074
He says, there shall be weeping and gnashing of teeth, when he shall see Abraham and Isaac and Jacob and all the prophets

13:53.218 --> 13:58.005
in the kingdom of God and you yourselves thrust out.

13:58.666 --> 14:05.056
And they shall come from the east and from the west and from the north and from the south and shall sit down in the kingdom of God.

14:05.096 --> 14:10.083
And behold, there are last which shall be first and then are first which shall be last."

14:10.103 --> 14:10.944
Same thing.

14:10.964 --> 14:19.877
But then in Mark 1313, our Lord makes a statement and more on the question of perseveuroms.

14:19.897 --> 14:22.962
And he shall be hated of all men for my name's sake.

14:23.298 --> 14:31.351
but he that shall endure unto the end the same shall be saved."

14:31.371 --> 14:31.751
Very well.

14:32.993 --> 14:45.493
Now then, there we have seen the actual history and we've seen that our Lord prophesied this very thing that happened to the Jews.

14:45.513 --> 14:51.602
The thing that the Apostle Paul is bemoaning and regret it is a thing

14:51.714 --> 14:54.897
that has already been dealt with by our law of Himself.

14:56.739 --> 15:13.016
But then having started in that way with the actual facts, the next step, it seems to me, is to find similar statements in the Scripture which seem to be teaching the same thing as this twenty-second verse in the 11th chapter of Romans seems to be teaching.

15:13.636 --> 15:17.200
And here, of course, you have these great passages.

15:17.320 --> 15:19.282
I read two of them at the beginning.

15:20.258 --> 15:37.943
That whole statement in John 15, and particularly the sixth verse, If a man had died not in me, he has cast forth as a trench and is wither, and men gather them and cast them into the fire, and they are burned.

15:39.285 --> 15:48.818
And again in one Corinthians 10, what the apostle is doing there is to remind the Corinthian Christians of how those children of Israel were God speaking.

15:49.090 --> 15:56.119
And they'd all been baptized into Moses, and they'd all passed into the same cloud, and they'd passed through the same Red Sea.

15:56.399 --> 15:59.924
But they didn't all arrive in the land of Canaan.

16:00.504 --> 16:07.413
Numbers of them, because they'd fallen into sin, various types have perished in the wilderness.

16:08.194 --> 16:17.746
And the Apostle says, all these things are written for our ensembles upon whom the ends of the world have come.

16:18.050 --> 16:30.253
Now there, you see, he is invoking this history and applying it to them in exactly the same way as he does here in this passage that we are looking at now.

16:30.273 --> 16:35.704
But then you get the same thing, of course, in certain well-known statements in the Epistle to the Hebrew.

16:36.626 --> 16:41.074
For instance, you get this in Hebrews 319.

16:43.298 --> 16:49.868
Well, we are told, so we see that they could not enter in because of unbelief.

16:51.210 --> 16:56.317
He's again referring back to the history of the children of Israel, with whom was he grieved forty years?

16:56.698 --> 17:03.828
Was it not with them that had sinned, whose carcasses fell in the wilderness, and to whom's wary that they should not enter into his breast?

17:04.249 --> 17:05.972
But to him that believed not.

17:06.432 --> 17:09.817
So we see that they could not enter in because of unbelief.

17:09.837 --> 17:13.042
Then the next chapter takes it up, let us therefore fear

17:13.154 --> 17:18.060
Unless the promise being left to us of entering into his rest, any of you should seem to come short of it.

17:18.480 --> 17:21.343
For unto us was the gospel preached as well as unto them.

17:21.944 --> 17:29.353
But the word preached did not profit them, not being mixed with faith in them that heard them.

17:29.373 --> 17:33.958
So you see, the emphasis seems to be upon the fact that it is our faith that matters.

17:34.479 --> 17:35.640
The gospel can be preached.

17:36.120 --> 17:40.946
But if we don't exercise this faith, well then it is of no value to us.

17:41.250 --> 17:51.873
And then, of course, with regard to the Christian of perseverance, everybody is familiar with the famous passage at the beginning of the sixth chapter of the Epistle to the Hebrews.

17:53.176 --> 17:55.761
Oh, how many souls have been tormented by this!

17:56.803 --> 18:01.714
It is impossible for those who are once enlightened and have tested of him the gift

18:01.954 --> 18:18.254
and were made partakers of the Holy Ghost and have tested the Word of God and the powers of the world to come, if they shall fall away, to renew them again and to repentance, seeing they crucified to themselves the Son of God afresh and put him to an open shame.

18:18.655 --> 18:22.540
And the parallel statement which is found in the tenth chapter.

18:22.760 --> 18:24.242
Well now, there is your evidence.

18:24.442 --> 18:30.930
There, at end of it, is the main evidence, facts, explicit teaching.

18:31.810 --> 18:42.641
And the question before us is, how can all this be reconciled with the other teaching which has already been put before us so plainly and so carefully?

18:43.021 --> 18:47.225
Well, I suggest to you that this is the method of procedure.

18:49.627 --> 18:55.193
We lay down, first of all, a general rule, a general principle of interpretation, which is this.

18:56.794 --> 19:00.498
Never base a doctrine on an isolated passage.

19:02.050 --> 19:03.492
Now, I think you'll all agree with that.

19:03.532 --> 19:05.195
You have to compare scripture with scripture.

19:05.896 --> 19:07.578
The scripture is a hurl.

19:08.299 --> 19:10.763
So, you start by just saying that.

19:11.945 --> 19:13.246
Here I come across something.

19:13.687 --> 19:18.094
I mustn't base my whole doctrine on this matter on an isolated state.

19:19.536 --> 19:21.178
Always take the whole of scripture.

19:22.420 --> 19:23.522
Scripture with scripture.

19:25.985 --> 19:29.330
Then, secondly, you can lay it down as a general principle.

19:29.570 --> 19:32.455
that the Scripture does not contradict itself.

19:33.636 --> 19:37.883
The Scripture is the Word of God, not the words of men, the Word of God.

19:37.943 --> 19:44.554
The Old Testament, the holy men of God speak as they were moved by the early Gospel.

19:44.574 --> 19:47.218
All Scripture is given by inspiration of God.

19:47.238 --> 19:49.421
It's all God-breathe.

19:49.742 --> 19:53.308
He breathes it in, all of it.

19:53.328 --> 19:57.394
And we have the statements with regard to the New Testament

19:57.922 --> 20:04.431
We have the testimony of Peter with regard to the writings of the Apostle Paul puts them with the other scriptures and so on.

20:05.092 --> 20:09.198
Very well then, because it is the word of God, it cannot contradict itself.

20:10.520 --> 20:15.988
There is always this agreement in the scripture, there are never any contradictions.

20:16.008 --> 20:24.721
You lay that down, I say again, as a fundamental postulate.

20:24.741 --> 20:25.362
Very well.

20:26.690 --> 20:34.058
Having said that in a general way, we go on now to make certain further statements.

20:35.960 --> 20:49.354
We have in the scriptures certain unmistakable statements, clever, explicit about which there is no difficulty at all concerning these essential points which we are considering.

20:50.194 --> 20:53.618
Now here again, I'd like to put that in the form of a principle.

20:55.042 --> 21:09.467
Whenever you find yourself confronted by a difficulty in the Scripture, something about which you're not quite clear, something about which you haven't exact knowledge, the principle now is always move from the known to the unknown.

21:11.170 --> 21:20.786
If you have a difficulty, we'll start with something about which you're certain and approach you a difficulty from a certain established position.

21:23.074 --> 21:25.897
I've often said that and I've given you various illustrations.

21:26.698 --> 21:30.562
It's what I've sometimes compared with taking a run if you want to jump over a hurdle.

21:31.383 --> 21:31.763
Go back.

21:32.464 --> 21:35.147
Don't stand too close to your problem if it's difficult.

21:35.207 --> 21:35.647
Go back.

21:36.048 --> 21:37.969
Go back to certain general positions.

21:38.210 --> 21:40.672
Go back to certain starting points.

21:40.692 --> 21:50.002
And then starting there with assurance you come forward and you'll find you're able to overcome this obstacle, you're able to jump over your further.

21:50.530 --> 21:57.278
Now, that I say means less, that you start with certain unmistakable teaching.

21:57.298 --> 22:07.890
And here it is, especially with regard to the doctrine of election and the doctrine of the final perseverance of the saints.

22:07.910 --> 22:18.002
Now, the moment you do that, you see, you find that this very chapter in which your difficulty arises in and of itself has something to say which helps you.

22:18.722 --> 22:24.310
You remember how the apostle began the old chapter, and I'm taking particularly to the second verse now.

22:24.551 --> 22:28.376
He says, God does not cast away his people, which he foreknew.

22:29.678 --> 22:34.045
That's the great principle, his people whom he foreknew.

22:35.246 --> 22:42.257
And then in verse 5 we saw it even, so then at this present time also there is a remnant according to the election of race.

22:44.480 --> 22:48.626
The apostasy of the Jewish nation was not total.

22:49.122 --> 22:52.768
The apostle reminds them that he was a believer and there were others.

22:54.070 --> 22:59.819
And this he describes as an elect, as a remnant, he has put an agreement according to the election of grace.

23:01.382 --> 23:02.083
Well, very well.

23:02.223 --> 23:11.097
And then we've gone on and have seen how as he goes forward the apostle is still continuing this same idea.

23:11.157 --> 23:14.002
This is the sole explanation.

23:14.114 --> 23:23.968
What then he says in verse 7, Israel is not obtained that which he seek for but the election has obtained it, and it's obtained it because it is the election, the rest were blinded and so on.

23:25.009 --> 23:29.095
So that our own chapter in and of itself helps us.

23:29.676 --> 23:34.903
If we ask ourselves now then what are the basic principles taught in the chapter?

23:35.143 --> 23:39.890
And at once you're reminded that it is this great doctrine of election.

23:40.354 --> 23:51.671
And that, of course, then reminds you that the apostle has been expounding that in detail and at length, especially in the ninth chapter, where we worked it out in detail.

23:53.273 --> 23:58.461
Where he puts it, of course, is so clearly, particularly in the 11th verse of that ninth chapter.

23:59.082 --> 24:09.618
The children being not yet born, neither having done any good or evil, that the purpose of God according to election might stand, not of works, but of him that call it.

24:10.178 --> 24:23.652
Now, the apostle has gone out of his way to show that the only manner in which you can understand the history of the Jews and the whole of the way of salvation is to see that it is according to the election of grace.

24:24.532 --> 24:29.137
There's no other explanation, and he's given us positive and negative arguments.

24:29.577 --> 24:38.066
He's put it in such a clear manner that when an objector comes forward, he says to him, nay, but oh men, who have thou that replies against God,

24:38.146 --> 24:40.689
Shall the thing formed, say to him that formed it?

24:40.709 --> 24:42.612
Why has the made made thus?

24:42.892 --> 24:49.781
Has not the pot of power over the clay of the same lump to make one vessel unto one another and another unto dishonor?"

24:49.801 --> 24:50.722
And so on.

24:50.742 --> 25:06.802
Now, there is this clear explicit statement with regard to this doctrine of election, that that is the only way of understanding why some are saved and some are not saved, the only way of understanding why anybody is saved.

25:07.522 --> 25:12.189
For it is clear that where it not for God's election, that there would be nobody saved at all.

25:13.070 --> 25:15.173
For we are all dead in trespasses and zeros.

25:15.494 --> 25:19.379
We are all men who have the natural mind, which is enmity against God.

25:19.419 --> 25:23.585
We are all natural men to whom the things of the Spirit of God are foolishness.

25:24.507 --> 25:25.929
We cannot understand them.

25:25.949 --> 25:26.610
It's impossible.

25:27.191 --> 25:27.631
Very well.

25:28.252 --> 25:29.894
We need to be quickened.

25:29.914 --> 25:35.122
It is the only explanation of how any single soul has ever been saved.

25:36.482 --> 25:39.105
